1
00:01:26,200 --> 00:01:27,319
You two, stop fooling around.

2
00:01:27,959 --> 00:01:29,000
So many people have shown up.

3
00:01:29,760 --> 00:01:30,359
Let me tell you,

4
00:01:30,840 --> 00:01:31,840
with this many Imperial Guards here,

5
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:32,799
this is no small matter.

6
00:01:33,840 --> 00:01:34,359
Ning Chen.

7
00:01:44,079 --> 00:01:45,719
Well, if it isn't handsome Quan.

8
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:47,840
Not attending His Majesty in the palace?

9
00:01:47,959 --> 00:01:48,760
Out for a stroll, are we?

10
00:01:49,280 --> 00:01:50,239
Silver Guard Ning,

11
00:01:50,879 --> 00:01:54,000
you've been quite hard to find.

12
00:01:55,760 --> 00:01:57,719
Eunuch Quan, let me explain.

13
00:01:58,359 --> 00:02:00,079
Too much explaining is a dead giveaway.

14
00:02:00,120 --> 00:02:00,840
Don't use your smile

15
00:02:00,920 --> 00:02:02,719
to mask the fear you feel toward me.

16
00:02:03,640 --> 00:02:04,439
Tell me,

17
00:02:05,040 --> 00:02:06,400
where are you hurt?

18
00:02:07,359 --> 00:02:08,599
Hurt?

19
00:02:09,080 --> 00:02:10,120
Silver Guard Ning.

20
00:02:11,120 --> 00:02:14,479
I meant, are your injuries all right?

21
00:02:19,360 --> 00:02:20,280
Me?

22
00:02:20,919 --> 00:02:22,159
My injuries?

23
00:02:22,599 --> 00:02:24,960
You could say I'm hurt,

24
00:02:25,759 --> 00:02:29,879
or you could say I'm only slightly hurt.

25
00:02:30,159 --> 00:02:31,319
It's all my fault,

26
00:02:32,479 --> 00:02:33,639
I was too reckless.

27
00:02:33,800 --> 00:02:34,479
You call that reckless?

28
00:02:34,639 --> 00:02:36,000
That was a blatant assault on me.

29
00:02:37,360 --> 00:02:37,919
Well...

30
00:02:38,960 --> 00:02:39,520
Look,

31
00:02:40,439 --> 00:02:42,439
this... this blatant wound,

32
00:02:43,240 --> 00:02:44,479
is it any better?

33
00:02:46,599 --> 00:02:48,199
I have quite the temper, you know.

34
00:02:48,879 --> 00:02:50,039
Don't think giving me a few things

35
00:02:50,719 --> 00:02:52,879
will calm me down.

36
00:02:54,759 --> 00:02:55,719
You... you...

37
00:02:55,879 --> 00:02:56,439
Feel any better?

38
00:02:57,280 --> 00:02:57,919
Better now?

39
00:03:00,120 --> 00:03:00,719
How about this?

40
00:03:01,360 --> 00:03:02,240
Has your anger faded?

41
00:03:02,560 --> 00:03:04,800
A misunderstanding! It's a misunderstanding.

42
00:03:04,960 --> 00:03:07,039
You were acting for His Majesty after all.

43
00:03:07,199 --> 00:03:09,159
I completely understand.

44
00:03:09,439 --> 00:03:11,240
Long live understanding!

45
00:03:11,400 --> 00:03:13,120
Long live understanding!

46
00:03:21,800 --> 00:03:22,719
Actually,

47
00:03:23,360 --> 00:03:24,400
there's one more matter

48
00:03:24,800 --> 00:03:25,800
I'd like to trouble you with, Eunuch Quan.

49
00:03:25,919 --> 00:03:26,520
Speak freely.

50
00:03:26,680 --> 00:03:27,280
Speak, speak.

51
00:03:27,879 --> 00:03:30,240
Please help me deliver these

52
00:03:30,919 --> 00:03:31,840
to the Ning Manor.

53
00:03:32,159 --> 00:03:33,080
I'll see to it at once.

54
00:03:34,159 --> 00:03:34,680
Rest assured.

55
00:03:35,280 --> 00:03:35,680
Good.

56
00:03:35,719 --> 00:03:36,719
Guards!

57
00:03:43,319 --> 00:03:43,800
Old Pan.

58
00:03:45,280 --> 00:03:45,800
What is it?

59
00:03:49,879 --> 00:03:50,879
What's all this about?

60
00:03:52,479 --> 00:03:53,000
What's going on?

61
00:03:58,080 --> 00:03:58,719
What do you mean?

62
00:03:59,639 --> 00:04:00,719
You're treating me like a dog too?

63
00:04:01,599 --> 00:04:02,560
What? I'm no lapdog.

64
00:04:02,719 --> 00:04:03,199
Let me tell you,

65
00:04:03,759 --> 00:04:04,240
Ning Chen.

66
00:04:05,080 --> 00:04:05,560
You...

67
00:04:06,280 --> 00:04:07,719
You've been at the Inspectorate a while now.

68
00:04:08,199 --> 00:04:09,879
This month's wages haven't been paid yet.

69
00:04:10,840 --> 00:04:11,400
I don't need it.

70
00:04:11,520 --> 00:04:12,080
You...

71
00:04:12,520 --> 00:04:13,520
Keep it for yourself.

72
00:04:14,919 --> 00:04:16,759
We're brothers, don't stand on ceremony.

73
00:04:17,040 --> 00:04:18,279
The gold's for you,

74
00:04:18,759 --> 00:04:21,279
and the silk's for Lady Nan Zhi.

75
00:04:22,560 --> 00:04:23,240
Old Pan,

76
00:04:24,079 --> 00:04:24,839
I'll be honest,

77
00:04:25,399 --> 00:04:27,160
at first I really disliked you.

78
00:04:27,800 --> 00:04:28,839
But after spending time together,

79
00:04:28,959 --> 00:04:29,839
I realized you're actually

80
00:04:30,720 --> 00:04:31,439
a pretty decent guy.

81
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:33,480
Thanks.

82
00:04:33,560 --> 00:04:33,920
Let's go.

83
00:04:34,240 --> 00:04:36,120
Tonight, the Music Bureau,

84
00:04:36,519 --> 00:04:37,160
my treat.

85
00:04:37,720 --> 00:04:39,680
Why do you never learn?

86
00:04:41,240 --> 00:04:43,000
I'm a Golden Guard of the Inspectorate.

87
00:04:43,120 --> 00:04:44,399
If I go to the Music Bureau with you daily,

88
00:04:44,600 --> 00:04:45,160
how would that look?

89
00:04:46,959 --> 00:04:47,759
Fine, don't come.

90
00:04:48,040 --> 00:04:48,879
I'll go with them.

91
00:04:50,600 --> 00:04:51,120
Ning Chen!

92
00:04:51,800 --> 00:04:52,720
I didn't say I wouldn't go.

93
00:04:54,199 --> 00:04:55,199
We've got to knock off work first, right?

94
00:04:55,879 --> 00:04:56,360
Right?

95
00:04:57,519 --> 00:04:58,240
Nan Zhi.

96
00:04:58,879 --> 00:05:00,040
Nan Zhi likes green.

97
00:05:04,079 --> 00:05:05,079
Knock off, knock off, let's knock off.

98
00:05:07,959 --> 00:05:08,800
Mother, look.

99
00:05:10,480 --> 00:05:11,360
Truly,

100
00:05:13,120 --> 00:05:14,279
all this fine silk and satin,

101
00:05:18,680 --> 00:05:19,959
we really are a family.

102
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:24,759
We could never spend all this.

103
00:05:26,120 --> 00:05:26,720
Chen'er,

104
00:05:27,439 --> 00:05:29,600
keeping all this money on you

105
00:05:29,959 --> 00:05:31,000
surely isn't safe.

106
00:05:31,519 --> 00:05:33,480
Let your father look after it for you.

107
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:34,839
Right, Fourth Brother.

108
00:05:35,480 --> 00:05:37,560
All this silk, satin, and gold,

109
00:05:38,240 --> 00:05:39,160
let's put it in the storeroom.

110
00:05:39,160 --> 00:05:39,639
It'll be safer.

111
00:05:41,360 --> 00:05:42,160
It's not safe.

112
00:05:43,959 --> 00:05:45,639
These are imperial gifts.

113
00:05:46,279 --> 00:05:47,680
Who'd dare steal them?

114
00:05:51,480 --> 00:05:52,399
This money,

115
00:05:53,160 --> 00:05:55,000
I'm going to use it to take a wife.

116
00:05:55,839 --> 00:05:57,480
Whoever dares lay a hand on it,

117
00:05:57,920 --> 00:05:59,680
I'll chop their hand off.

118
00:06:03,439 --> 00:06:04,439
Wait a minute, Chen'er.

119
00:06:04,560 --> 00:06:06,360
Don't you have a sweetheart

120
00:06:06,879 --> 00:06:07,800
at the Music Bureau?

121
00:06:09,240 --> 00:06:11,160
Lord Ning's quite well-informed.

122
00:06:11,839 --> 00:06:12,920
So it's true.

123
00:06:13,360 --> 00:06:14,360
I'm warning you,

124
00:06:14,560 --> 00:06:16,560
I will absolutely not let some courtesan

125
00:06:16,680 --> 00:06:17,759
step through our gates

126
00:06:17,959 --> 00:06:19,079
and disgrace the Ning family name.

127
00:06:19,639 --> 00:06:21,279
Yu Die may be a courtesan,

128
00:06:21,480 --> 00:06:22,839
but she's pure and untainted.

129
00:06:23,759 --> 00:06:26,000
Compared to you, who does nothing but sneer

130
00:06:26,160 --> 00:06:27,800
and scheme with petty malice, Madam,

131
00:06:27,959 --> 00:06:29,000
she's far better.

132
00:06:29,759 --> 00:06:30,759
You scoundrel, you!

133
00:06:30,959 --> 00:06:31,480
Ning Chen!

134
00:06:31,639 --> 00:06:32,800
How dare you speak to your mother like that?

135
00:06:33,120 --> 00:06:33,639
Ning Chen,

136
00:06:34,120 --> 00:06:36,040
your mother fed and clothed you all these years,

137
00:06:36,279 --> 00:06:36,920
and in the end,

138
00:06:37,079 --> 00:06:38,639
this is how you repay her?

139
00:06:39,079 --> 00:06:40,560
My lord, just look at him.

140
00:06:40,800 --> 00:06:42,480
Does he even see me as his mother?

141
00:06:44,720 --> 00:06:45,920
You're defying your elders,

142
00:06:46,079 --> 00:06:47,399
this is utterly unfilial!

143
00:06:48,199 --> 00:06:50,000
Fine. If Yudie can't enter the Ning Manor,

144
00:06:50,279 --> 00:06:51,279
then I'll follow Guo Qiling's example.

145
00:06:51,519 --> 00:06:52,519
I'll let her marry me instead.

146
00:06:52,720 --> 00:06:53,480
I'll move into her household.

147
00:06:55,600 --> 00:06:57,279
Who the hell does Guo Qiling think he is?

148
00:06:58,319 --> 00:06:59,959
I'm laying it down right here, right now,

149
00:07:00,680 --> 00:07:02,759
these things belong to the Ning Manor.

150
00:07:03,199 --> 00:07:04,160
That whore

151
00:07:04,360 --> 00:07:06,600
will never set foot in the Ning Manor.

152
00:07:09,480 --> 00:07:10,600
After all that talk,

153
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:12,560
you just want these things, don't you?

154
00:07:13,360 --> 00:07:14,439
You should've said so sooner.

155
00:07:14,639 --> 00:07:15,600
I would have just given them to you.

156
00:07:15,759 --> 00:07:16,240
Take it all.

157
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:17,160
Really?

158
00:07:24,759 --> 00:07:25,399
Let me grab one more.

159
00:07:26,600 --> 00:07:27,240
Seriously.

160
00:07:29,800 --> 00:07:30,800
Imperial Inspectorate, on official duty.

161
00:07:31,279 --> 00:07:32,720
Everyone stay where you are.

162
00:07:33,480 --> 00:07:34,360
Anyone who disobeys

163
00:07:35,120 --> 00:07:35,759
will be executed.

164
00:07:38,480 --> 00:07:39,720
You're really letting a little power

165
00:07:41,160 --> 00:07:41,959
go to your head, aren't you?

166
00:07:45,480 --> 00:07:47,240
Stealing items bestowed by the Emperor,

167
00:07:47,439 --> 00:07:48,560
showing contempt for imperial authority.

168
00:07:49,079 --> 00:07:50,199
The crime is unforgivable.

169
00:07:50,839 --> 00:07:51,399
Everyone,

170
00:07:51,879 --> 00:07:53,680
come with me to the Inspectorate for trial.

171
00:07:57,560 --> 00:07:58,360
Listen to me.

172
00:07:58,920 --> 00:08:00,759
Don't go pinning false charges on us.

173
00:08:01,000 --> 00:08:02,160
My father is the Left Chancellor.

174
00:08:02,560 --> 00:08:03,920
I dare you to lay a finger on us.

175
00:08:05,519 --> 00:08:06,000
Madam,

176
00:08:06,560 --> 00:08:07,720
the law shows no mercy.

177
00:08:08,439 --> 00:08:09,839
As a Silver Guard of the Inspectorate,

178
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:11,240
deeply trusted by His Majesty,

179
00:08:11,879 --> 00:08:13,120
I must lead by example

180
00:08:13,279 --> 00:08:14,240
and uphold the law fairly.

181
00:08:15,040 --> 00:08:15,800
So,

182
00:08:16,800 --> 00:08:18,800
today I'm raiding the Ning Manor.

183
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:21,759
If any of you dare to interfere,

184
00:08:22,800 --> 00:08:23,959
I'll deal with you.

185
00:08:24,839 --> 00:08:26,319
If the Left Chancellor dares interfere,

186
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:28,600
I'll deal with him too.

187
00:08:35,440 --> 00:08:35,960
Mother.

188
00:08:36,480 --> 00:08:37,399
What do we do, Mother?

189
00:08:38,039 --> 00:08:40,120
He's not really taking us to the Inspectorate, is he?

190
00:08:40,639 --> 00:08:41,639
That place is a living hell.

191
00:08:41,799 --> 00:08:43,120
No one ever comes back from there.

192
00:08:43,240 --> 00:08:45,200
Mother, I don't want to go to the Inspectorate.

193
00:08:45,360 --> 00:08:46,399
Calm down, calm down.

194
00:08:47,440 --> 00:08:49,000
Say something!

195
00:08:53,879 --> 00:08:54,440
Chen'er.

196
00:08:55,279 --> 00:08:56,120
Just tell your father,

197
00:08:56,559 --> 00:08:57,360
what exactly do you want?

198
00:08:59,440 --> 00:09:00,840
Honestly, what's with His Majesty?

199
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:02,080
Couldn't he just give us a banknote?

200
00:09:02,519 --> 00:09:03,559
So many gold bricks,

201
00:09:03,720 --> 00:09:04,679
we can't even carry them.

202
00:09:05,200 --> 00:09:05,840
Lord Ning,

203
00:09:06,759 --> 00:09:08,360
today was just a warning.

204
00:09:09,559 --> 00:09:10,840
If you want your three sons

205
00:09:10,960 --> 00:09:12,159
to stay alive,

206
00:09:13,879 --> 00:09:15,600
let me bring Yudie home as my wife.

207
00:09:27,240 --> 00:09:28,080
This color looks lovely.

208
00:09:28,240 --> 00:09:29,480
The fabric's nice too. So festive.

209
00:09:39,200 --> 00:09:40,080
What's wrong, Yudie?

210
00:09:40,759 --> 00:09:41,399
Why are you crying?

211
00:09:42,080 --> 00:09:42,799
I don't know.

212
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:45,120
Just thinking of you going to war

213
00:09:45,799 --> 00:09:46,879
makes me want to cry.

214
00:09:49,879 --> 00:09:50,519
It's all right.

215
00:09:52,080 --> 00:09:52,799
Don't worry.

216
00:09:53,519 --> 00:09:54,600
I'll take good care of myself.

217
00:09:55,120 --> 00:09:56,000
Blades have no mercy.

218
00:09:56,600 --> 00:09:57,519
It's so dangerous.

219
00:09:58,360 --> 00:09:58,960
Don't worry.

220
00:09:59,639 --> 00:10:00,159
Oh, right.

221
00:10:01,159 --> 00:10:02,000
His Majesty has promised me

222
00:10:02,519 --> 00:10:03,720
that if I make it back alive,

223
00:10:04,240 --> 00:10:05,480
he'll release you from servitude

224
00:10:05,879 --> 00:10:07,039
and restore your freedom.

225
00:10:07,480 --> 00:10:09,799
Even so, I don't want you fighting on the battlefield.

226
00:10:10,320 --> 00:10:11,279
It's far too dangerous.

227
00:10:13,600 --> 00:10:14,200
For your sake,

228
00:10:15,679 --> 00:10:16,279
I'm willing.

229
00:10:22,600 --> 00:10:24,240
Madam, what brings you here?

230
00:10:24,480 --> 00:10:26,320
I've got something good to show you.

231
00:10:27,240 --> 00:10:28,000
A few years ago,

232
00:10:28,080 --> 00:10:30,399
a wandering warrior visited our Music Bureau.

233
00:10:30,720 --> 00:10:31,960
He didn't leave the bed for ten days,

234
00:10:32,399 --> 00:10:33,639
went through more than a dozen girls.

235
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:36,320
The bastard ran out of money afterward,

236
00:10:36,519 --> 00:10:37,360
so he handed over this prescription

237
00:10:37,759 --> 00:10:38,960
to settle the bill.

238
00:10:43,919 --> 00:10:44,559
Is that so?

239
00:10:45,799 --> 00:10:46,799
According to him,

240
00:10:47,080 --> 00:10:49,000
this prescription is priceless.

241
00:10:49,120 --> 00:10:50,600
Whether brewed or used in a medicinal bath,

242
00:10:50,759 --> 00:10:52,840
it does wonders for the body.

243
00:10:53,679 --> 00:10:54,759
It strengthens the body,

244
00:10:54,840 --> 00:10:56,840
keeps your vital energy flowing,

245
00:10:56,960 --> 00:11:00,000
and makes a man full of vigor.

246
00:11:00,240 --> 00:11:01,799
I had someone test it later,

247
00:11:02,000 --> 00:11:02,840
and it really does work.

248
00:11:05,080 --> 00:11:06,200
Ancient Wei.

249
00:11:08,720 --> 00:11:09,399
I don't need it.

250
00:11:11,360 --> 00:11:13,519
Silver Guard Ning, drop the act.

251
00:11:13,840 --> 00:11:16,799
You've got such a frail little frame.

252
00:11:17,200 --> 00:11:19,320
Compared to the other Silver Guards at the Inspectorate,

253
00:11:19,440 --> 00:11:20,519
you're really nothing special.

254
00:11:20,720 --> 00:11:22,879
I just think you're a decent fellow,

255
00:11:23,399 --> 00:11:24,240
so this prescription,

256
00:11:24,679 --> 00:11:26,919
it's yours, free of charge.

257
00:11:28,320 --> 00:11:29,240
I'm nothing special?

258
00:11:30,399 --> 00:11:31,519
I'm nothing special?

259
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:36,720
I'd say you're just okay.

260
00:11:36,840 --> 00:11:38,320
What's that supposed to mean?

261
00:11:38,440 --> 00:11:39,000
Well, I...

262
00:11:40,720 --> 00:11:41,399
Yudie, you see,

263
00:11:41,759 --> 00:11:42,919
hasn't been with any other man.

264
00:11:43,559 --> 00:11:45,840
But compared to your colleagues in the Inspectorate,

265
00:11:46,200 --> 00:11:48,320
you're really quite ordinary.

266
00:11:59,879 --> 00:12:00,759
Well, thanks.

267
00:12:01,480 --> 00:12:02,840
You're welcome.

268
00:12:03,000 --> 00:12:03,679
I'm only

269
00:12:03,879 --> 00:12:04,879
thinking of Yudie's

270
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:06,840
future happiness, you know.

271
00:12:09,639 --> 00:12:10,679
It's so hot in here.

272
00:12:11,720 --> 00:12:13,600
Why's it so hot all of a sudden?

273
00:12:18,840 --> 00:12:19,720
Actually,

274
00:12:20,480 --> 00:12:21,759
it's not that hot, is it?

275
00:12:22,799 --> 00:12:24,080
Thank you, Lord Ning.

276
00:12:24,200 --> 00:12:25,240
I won't disturb you any further.

277
00:12:25,360 --> 00:12:26,519
Carry on, you two.

278
00:12:32,080 --> 00:12:32,720
Now then,

279
00:12:33,360 --> 00:12:35,840
allow me to attend to your bath, my lord.

280
00:12:36,600 --> 00:12:37,519
A medicinal bath.

281
00:12:39,519 --> 00:12:40,120
Sounds good.

282
00:12:48,360 --> 00:12:49,000
Who is it?

283
00:12:49,559 --> 00:12:50,080
Lord Ning.

284
00:12:50,320 --> 00:12:51,879
Brother Mei, please, save my sister!

285
00:12:52,320 --> 00:12:52,960
What happened to Xiaomei?

286
00:12:53,440 --> 00:12:54,440
You may not know this, my lord.

287
00:12:54,799 --> 00:12:56,639
A few days ago, Xiaomei was out shopping,

288
00:12:56,799 --> 00:12:58,320
and Hu Qiang of the Hu family took a fancy to her.

289
00:12:58,639 --> 00:13:00,679
Today the Hu family came and dragged her away.

290
00:13:00,840 --> 00:13:01,720
I tried to reason with them,

291
00:13:01,840 --> 00:13:03,080
and they beat me up for it.

292
00:13:03,480 --> 00:13:05,000
Xiaomei still hasn't come back.

293
00:13:06,639 --> 00:13:07,840
Why didn't you come to me sooner?

294
00:13:08,559 --> 00:13:09,039
I...

295
00:13:11,519 --> 00:13:11,919
Die'er,

296
00:13:12,360 --> 00:13:13,080
something urgent has come up.

297
00:13:13,440 --> 00:13:14,039
Wait for me to return.

298
00:13:15,919 --> 00:13:16,360
Lead the way.

